%h1 Kollision

%p
  Die folgenden Buchungen in der
  %strong= @blocking.calendar.villa.name
  überschneiden sich:

- style = { align: "left", style: "border: solid #9D9D9D; border-width: 1px 0" }
%table.table{ border: 0, cellpadding: 0, cellspacing: 0, style: "border-collapse: collapse" }
  %tr
    %th{ style } Nr.
    %th{ style } Kalender
    %th{ style } Beginn
    %th{ style } Ende

  %tr
    %td{ style }= link_to @blocking.number, edit_admin_blocking_url(@blocking)
    %td{ style }
      = @blocking.calendar.clash_email_name
      (extern)
    %td{ style }= l @blocking.start_date
    %td{ style }= l @blocking.end_date

  %tr
    %td{ style }= link_to @booking.number, [:edit, :admin, @booking]
    %td{ style } Intervilla (intern)
    %td{ style }= l @booking.start_date
    %td{ style }= l @booking.end_date
  %tr
    %th{ style.merge(align: "right", colspan: 2) }
      Überschneidung
    %td{ style }= l @clash.begin
    %td{ style }= l @clash.end

%p
  Dieser Konflikt muss manuell gelöst werden:
  = link_to "zum Belegungskalender", occupancies_calendar_admin_villa_url(@booking.villa, year: @clash.begin.year)
